Five people are in custody after officers conducted crime prevention operations targeted at suspected gangsters in Elsies River and Steenberg on Thursday night, Western Cape police said on Friday. In Steenberg, a 40-year-old suspect was arrested for being in possession of a prohibited firearm, a .38 Special and six round of ammunition, police spokesman Andre Traut said in a statement. In Elsies River, a 23-year-old suspect was arrested for being in possession of 37 x 7.65 rounds. A 22-year old man was arrested on drug possession charges in Leonsdale, Elsies River. Officers found him with seven packets of tik, ten already rolled dagga (marijuana) cigarettes, and seven mandrax tablets. At another location in the same area police arrested a suspect for being in possession of nine parcels of dagga. The final arrest was a 20-year-old suspect who was caught in possession of a prohibited 7.65 firearm and five rounds of ammunition, also in Elsies River, said Traut. The suspects were all expected to appear in court on Monday. African News Agency For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.